Line a small sheet pan with non stick aluminum foil. Arrange salmon on baking sheet. Brush fish fillets with 2 Tbsp. of reserved pineapple juice. Sprinkle fillets evenly with 2 Tbsp. of Mrs. Dash(R) Original Blend. Bake in middle of 375 degrees F preheated oven, about 4-5 minutes or until fish starts to flake slightly. Combine all other ingredients in medium bowl. Serve fish, spooning fresh salsa alongside.